{"questionId":"12927","questionHtml":"<p>One of the roots <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{w_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>w</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> satisfies the condition <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{Re}}\\left( {{w_1}} \\right) = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Re</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>w</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Given that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{w_1} = \\frac{z}{{z - {\\text{i}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>w</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>z</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;express <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n</math></span> in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + b{\\text{i}}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>i</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b \\in \\mathbb{Q}\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{w_1} =&nbsp; - 2{\\text{i}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>w</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>i</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{z}{{z - {\\text{i}}}} =&nbsp; - 2{\\text{i}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>z</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>i</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z =&nbsp; - 2{\\text{i}}\\left( {z - {\\text{i}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>i</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\\left( {1 + 2{\\text{i}}} \\right) =&nbsp; - 2\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z = \\frac{{ - 2}}{{1 + 2{\\text{i}}}}\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z =&nbsp; - \\frac{2}{5} + \\frac{4}{5}{\\text{i}}\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>i</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a =&nbsp; - \\frac{2}{5}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b = \\frac{4}{5}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12927","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"One of the roots w 1 satisfies the condition Re ( w 1 ) = 0 . Given that w 1 = z z − i , express z in the form a + b i , where a , b ∈ Q .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Complex roots of polynomials, conjugate roots, De Moivre’s, powers & roots of complex numbers"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}